race.comment: GOODELLO (13) ran a solid race on debut, finishing just over a length behind the winner in third over 1100m at Werribee 3 weeks ago. The extra 200m will help, and he looks capable of sharp improvement. On top this time. QISMAH (11) returns from a six-month spell and has been tuned up with some impressive recent jumpout form. The blinkers go on for the first time today, and she is a genuine each-way contender. HOT STEPPING HIPPY (10) took a step forward last start, finishing a solid third over 1170m at Wangaratta. This is a race with more depth, but further improvement is on the cards. SO STAR (8) won the latest of his 6 public jumpouts, and he has a bit of breeding about him. Let the market be your best guide, but he should make the grade. OMINOUS (7) has looked promising at the trials, and he hails from the in-form Grahame Begg stable, which automatically makes him one to watch.
